"title": "2575: Jesus Christ, temptation of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2575",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Repeated yet unsuccessful efforts made by Satan and by human beings to deflect Jesus Christ from his Father's will.</p>\n<h2>The wilderness temptations</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:13\">MRK 1:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Tempted to turn stones into bread</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:2-Matt4:3\">MAT 4:2–4:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:2-Luke4:3\">LUK 4:2–4:3</a></p>\n<h3>Tempted to abuse miraculous power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:5-Matt4:6\">MAT 4:5–4:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:9-Luke4:11\">LUK 4:9–4:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:38\">MAT 12:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:1\">MAT 16:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:11\">MRK 8:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:16\">LUK 11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:18\">JHN 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Tempted by the offer of an easy route to power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:8-Matt4:9\">MAT 4:8–4:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:5-Luke4:7\">LUK 4:5–4:7</a></p>\n<h3>Tempted to doubt he was God's Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:3\">MAT 4:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:3\">LUK 4:3</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:6\">MAT 4:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:9\">LUK 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:40\">MAT 27:40</a></p>\n<h2>Temptation continued throughout Jesus Christ's life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:28\">LUK 22:28</a></strong> <em>Trials can include temptations.</em></p>\n<h3>Opponents tempted Jesus Christ with trick questions</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:15\">MAT 22:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:13\">MRK 12:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:20\">LUK 20:20</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ tempted to sidestep the cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21-Matt16:23\">MAT 16:21–16:23</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:32-Mark8:33\">MRK 8:32–8:33</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39-Matt26:44\">MAT 26:39–26:44</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:35-Mark14:41\">MRK 14:35–14:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:41-Luke22:44\">LUK 22:41–22:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:40\">MAT 27:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:30\">MRK 15:30</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ steadfastly resisted temptation</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ resisted temptation by trusting God's word</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:4\">MAT 4:4</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:4\">LUK 4:4</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:7\">MAT 4:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:12\">LUK 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:10\">MAT 4:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:8\">LUK 4:8</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ resisted temptation by obeying his Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:7-Heb5:8\">HEB 5:7–5:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:36\">MRK 14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:42\">MAT 26:42</a></p>\n<h2>Results of Jesus Christ's temptations</h2>\n<h3>Satan left Jesus Christ alone</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:11\">MAT 4:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:13\">LUK 4:13</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ remained sinless</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15\">HEB 4:15</a></strong> <em>Refers to Jesus Christ as high priest and as sacrificial lamb.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:46\">JHN 8:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:22\">1PE 2:22</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ helps those who are being tempted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:18\">HEB 2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:14-Heb4:16\">HEB 4:14–4:16</a></p>",
